# React Component Syntax

## Context

- This rule applies to all React component definitions in JSX and TSX files
- Components should be defined using arrow function syntax with const declarations
- Default exports should use the `export default ComponentName` syntax when appropriate

## Requirements

- Always define React components using arrow function syntax with const declarations
- Always follow the pattern: `const ComponentName = () => { return (...) }` or `const ComponentName = () => (...)`
- Always use PascalCase for component names
- Always for default exports of components, use `export default ComponentName` syntax
